 Centane - Centane police have opened an inquest docket after a 27-year old man who was reported missing, was found dead. "The 27-year-old man by the name of Zwelethu Njama was last seen on Saturday, 9 May 2020 at about 16h00, at Gaqa Locality, Nxaxo Village, Centane," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "He was reported as a missing person. Centane Police assisted by East London Police Search and Rescue Unit along with the members of the community of Nxaxo Village searched for the missing person with negative results." He said that the deceased was found by a passer-by, floating in the river at Gaqa Locality, Nxaxo Village, Centane on Sunday, 17 May 2020 at about 07h00 in the morning. "The body of the deceased had no visible injuries and his cellphone was found with him." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 